{
  "doc_id": "17774",
  "text": "The association between advanced age and the thiamine concentration has not been conclusively determined [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Ito et al. recently found that more than half of nursing home elderly residents had a low wholeblood thiamine concentration (,20 ng/mL) as evaluated at an institution in Japan [CITATION_4] . A high incidence of low thiamine concentrations among hospitalized elderly patients in the Japanese population has therefore been anticipated.",
